   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the plate in the bottom of the UPS cabinet and lift
up the second plate that covers the busbars.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/0g_pxcupsn025_measure_for_voltages_0000181046.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Connect the equipment grounding conductor to the ground
busbar.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/50_kva_connect_power_cables_connect_ground_cable_120mm_0000104279.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         translate="no"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Use a probe to measure for voltages and currents at the
busbars:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>UPS input at input L1, input L2, input L3 , and input
N.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Bypass at bypass L1, bypass L2, bypass L3, and bypass
N.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>UPS output at output L1, output L2, output L3, and output
N.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Battery DC at battery + and battery - .</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig expanse="page">
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/50_kva_connect_power_cables_to_terminals_120mm_0000104237.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         translate="no"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig expanse="page">
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet and Transformer Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality__50_kw_diups50ditransf_connectdualcables_w170mm_0000162094.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
      </ol>
